<br>
I believe the wizards need a boost.  But how?  Here is my list of what the wizards need.<br>
<br>
1) AE needs to be made legal.  Currently AE tactics violate VI's Play nice policies.  Before flaming please read the play nice policies so we can discuss.<br>
2) Vel mobs need their resistances reduced.  Yes they are working on this.  But at 51 the prime targets are Ice based giants, yet Draught of fire rarly hits without additional assistance.<br>
3) VI needs to have a policy to investigate the wizard class every 3-4 months, to reevalulate how the latest changes affect the wizard class.  The continual improvements being added to melee classes and nothing added to the wizard class is what is causing the current rift between the two.<br>
4) Wizard DD needs to count more towards exp for the group.  The way it used to be was 3 wizards could evenly distribute exp between 3 groups.  That is no longer the case.  Now the pulling group gets all the exp.<br>
5) VI needs to look at the damage per second of the wizard class compared to all other classes.  I am counting damage / casting time + recast time + recovery time + meditation time.  OR<br>
5) VI needs to make the wizard class more of a support orientated class, with spells to match.<br>
6) The other classes need more AE orientated spells and or weapons so that AE tactics are not so scary to the &quot;pig headed&quot; tank.<br>
7) Quit putting out expansions.  Every expansion wizards have gotten worse.  Drop the idea that Melee is supposed to be the &quot;best&quot; and balance all the classes.<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Balance the races.  As a wizard by level 16 all the races are the same with the exception of the Dark-elves.  This is the reason no one starts a human wizard any longer, (but then who starts a wizard period).  <br>
9) Increase the AC of a couple mobs.  That way wizards are needed in more battles than just the super god mobs that wizards are only needed for currently.  Increased AC would balance out the Golems in Hate, and other places, that are currently immune to magic.  Lures are nice, but you have to have them first.  And Lures are not the holy grail NO SPELL IS.<br>
<br>
If VI would only accept 1 of these suggestions the wizard class will still not be fixed.  VI needs to accept 3 of these 10 before I start up my wizard again.  Then continual work to maintain and / or improve the class.<br>
<br>
And to those that believe wizards are balanced I empathize.  But can you still say that the class would be worse off with these improvements?  I do not want to be the most powerful class, although through all we have to go through maybe we should be by level 60, I want to be useful to my group, and guild.  For more than just ports.  I would be willing to give up ports if VI would implement all these suggestions. <br>
<br>
Sorry for the length but I could expand to longer than this for each one of those suggestions.  I am assuming if you don not understand a point you will ask for further clarification.<br>
<br>
Damoen Stuka<br>
